<P>
With FERC's expanded enforcement scope and civil penalty authority under =
EPAct 2005 and the addition of mandatory reliability requirements develop=
ed by the ERO, energy industry companies are anxious about how the new en=
forcement regime will affect them. =20
<P>
One thing is certain though. Under FERC's October 2005 Enforcement Policy=
, companies with formalized and effective compliance programs will not on=
ly be more likely to avoid violations, but if one occurs, will be in a po=
sition to potentially receive a reduced or even fully-mitigated civil pen=
alty.</font><font face=3D"tahoma, Arial, Verdana, Helvectia"><P align=3D"=
center">
<b>&nbsp;<br>
<a onmouseover=3D"showtitle(this,'P012090')" title=3D"P012090" href=3D'ht=
tp://cmgr.netcontentinc.net/chandler/proxy.aspx=3Flid=3DB105E851-E8D1-4AD=
5-A368-12685F7DACBD'>
<u>Registration - Single Site: $245.00</u></a></b><P align=3D"center">
<b>
<a onmouseover=3D"showtitle(this,'P012091')" title=3D"P012091" href=3D'ht=
tp://cmgr.netcontentinc.net/chandler/proxy.aspx=3Flid=3D9A3BBD16-FB81-4F8=
5-84A3-4BC3BBD019B9'>
<u>Registration - Additional Site: $150.00</u></a></b></font><font size=3D=
"2" face=3D"tahoma, Arial, Verdana, Helvectia"><P>

<P>

This webinar will address the elements of an effective FERC compliance pr=
ogram, useful tools for implementing such a program, and how the complian=
ce program successfully interfaces with other compliance processes alread=
y in place.  In addition, because a potential violation might even result=
 in criminal charges, the speakers will focus on the special consideratio=
ns of handling these matters.  To provide a broader perspective, the spea=
kers will also address important lessons learned from designing analogous=
 compliance programs in other highly regulated industries.  Finally, whet=
her your company already has a compliance program or needs one, the webin=
ar will conclude with strategies on how to assess the effectiveness of yo=
ur current compliance capabilities.
<P>
Join the experts at Ballard Spahr for a 90-minute, comprehensive and prac=
tical discussion of how to develop and maintain an effective FERC complia=
nce program


